A '''sucker-punch''' is an unannounced attack made with a closed fist. The most common types are sudden blows to the [[stomach]], mostly aiming for the [[Celiac plexus|solar plexus]], causing one to lose one's breath. However, sucker-punching is also colloquially associated with striking someone from the back without a warning.

Alternately, the name refers to any punch for which the opponent is unprepared and therefore cannot defend against. It is seen as a dishonourable yet effective opening tactic.

